<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="455" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1901,2034]" pageId="4" pageNumber="455">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1901,1926]" pageId="4" pageNumber="455">Remarks.</emphasis>
Published descriptions of the larva derive from 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad" box="[806,997,1901,1926]" pageId="4" pageNumber="455" refString="Lundblad, O. (1930) Die Hydracarinen der Insel Bornholm. Kongelige Danske Videnskabernes Selskab, Biologiske Meddelelser, 8, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1930">Lundblad (1930)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets" box="[1008,1147,1901,1926]" pageId="4" pageNumber="455" refString="Viets, K. (1936) Wassermilben oder Hydracarina (Hydrachnellae und Halacaridae). In: Dahl, F. (Ed.), Die Tierwelt Deutschlands und der angrenzenden Meeresteile nach ihren Merkmalen und ihrer Lebensweise. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Jena, 575 pp." type="book" year="1936">Viets (1936)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin" box="[1201,1353,1901,1926]" pageId="4" pageNumber="455" refString="Martin, P. (2000) Larval morphology and host-parasite associations of some stream living water mites (Hydrachnidia, Acari). Archiv fur Hydrobiologie / Supplement, 121 / 3 - 4, Monographical Studies, 269 - 320." type="journal article" year="2000">Martin (2000</bibRefCitation>
, 2006). As 
<taxonomicName box="[189,295,1937,1962]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[189,295,1937,1962]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="455">L. glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is monospecific in the 
<taxonomicName box="[558,685,1937,1962]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="455" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lebertiidae</taxonomicName>
of the Lurenzgriecht, the species is easy to key out from the other larvae by using the genus characters, e.g. CXII+III truncate posteriorly or setae 
<date box="[1072,1200,1973,1998]" pageId="4" pageNumber="455">V1 and V2</date>
located on posterior edges of CXIII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
